WEBVTT

00:37.287 --> 00:39.471
<i>There is</i>
<i> an old, oblique scar...</i>

00:41.342 --> 00:43.142
<i> three-quarter inches...</i>

00:44.578 --> 00:46.545
<i> at the mid third</i>
<i> of the upper lip.</i>

00:47.715 --> 00:48.614
<i>Ooh!</i>

00:50.901 --> 00:53.185
- The scar ends at the
anterior of the hairline.

00:53.187 --> 00:57.156
There is a flattening of the
prominence at the junction

00:57.158 --> 00:59.158
of the bony portion
of the nasal bone

00:59.160 --> 01:00.826
and the cartilaginous septum.

01:02.830 --> 01:06.765
Extending across the upper
lip to the left nostril

01:06.767 --> 01:10.069
is an odd, irregular scar
seven-eighths by one-eighths

01:10.071 --> 01:13.672
that ends at the
mucocutaneous border.

01:16.210 --> 01:16.809
- Uh!

01:36.564 --> 01:38.130
No goal!

01:38.132 --> 01:40.199
- Suture cross
scars are present.

01:40.201 --> 01:42.234
<i> Scar ends at the</i>
<i> lower right lip.</i>

01:46.474 --> 01:48.440
<i> A vertical linear scar</i>

01:48.442 --> 01:50.109
on the right upper lip

01:50.111 --> 01:52.511
<i> looks to have</i>
<i> come from youth.</i>

02:00.488 --> 02:02.605
Come on, guys!

02:02.606 --> 02:04.723
<i>Winter white</i>
<i> light like a sword in the sun.</i>

02:06.160 --> 02:08.360
Terry, keep your
fingers off the screen!

02:08.362 --> 02:11.163
<i> Warm nights under quilts;</i>

02:11.165 --> 02:13.265
<i> whispers back and forth;</i>

02:13.267 --> 02:15.601
<i> saves and misses.</i>

02:15.603 --> 02:17.536
How'd you know
he was gonna shoot it high?

02:17.538 --> 02:19.638
'Cause it looked like he
was going to shoot it--

02:19.640 --> 02:21.774
- Terry, you got to know.

02:21.775 --> 02:23.909
The goalie's the punching bag if
you lose. And hero if you win.

02:23.911 --> 02:26.178
<i> I'd tell Mitch he was mental</i>

02:26.180 --> 02:27.546
<i> playing goal.</i>

02:27.548 --> 02:29.348
- Anybody's girl would
rather be with you.

02:29.350 --> 02:31.416
- Hey, wait. Wait, which girls?

02:32.586 --> 02:33.585
- Uh!

02:33.587 --> 02:34.887
- Terry!

02:36.557 --> 02:38.590
<i>You all right?</i>

02:40.728 --> 02:43.896
- Buffalo's getting
a team next season.

02:46.934 --> 02:49.601
Buffalo.

02:49.603 --> 02:53.172
Spent a month
there one night.

03:04.919 --> 03:06.285
<i> He's in there.</i>

03:06.287 --> 03:07.519
<i> Red!?</i>

03:09.423 --> 03:10.756
<i>Game's gone now.</i>

03:10.758 --> 03:13.759
I hardly ever
watch it anymore.

03:14.595 --> 03:16.395
Cheerleaders.

03:19.800 --> 03:21.867
Kids who train
in a boxing ring.

03:21.869 --> 03:24.236
What's that got to
do with a puck and a net?

03:24.238 --> 03:25.904
<i> It's his first in nine.</i>

03:27.657 --> 03:29.407
<i> And the game's all</i>
<i> tied up one-one.</i>

03:29.410 --> 03:32.377
- What was it I was
going on about?

03:32.379 --> 03:36.481
Oh. You know, an athlete
used to live in the moment.

03:37.751 --> 03:41.353
It's in my memories that I live.

03:41.855 --> 03:45.224
Oh. Terry Sawchuk.

03:45.226 --> 03:48.260
I remember Terry Sawchuk.

03:48.262 --> 03:52.231
Ah, how could you get
a handle on a guy like him?

03:54.268 --> 03:56.268
Yeah.

04:00.341 --> 04:03.242
Sawchuk.

04:03.244 --> 04:05.811
Even his name,

04:05.813 --> 04:08.447
it means hockey to me.

04:09.383 --> 04:11.316
<i> And, uh, when I'm</i>

04:11.318 --> 04:15.354
<i> picking my team in</i>
<i> the afterlife? Hm.</i>

04:15.623 --> 04:19.391
He'll be backstopping
us for sure.

04:20.861 --> 04:22.995
Would he know that?

04:23.931 --> 04:25.764
<i>Are we on yet?</i>

04:25.766 --> 04:28.217
<i> Hello, Canada!</i>

04:28.218 --> 04:30.669
<i> And hockey fans in the</i>
<i>United States and Newfoundland.</i>

04:30.671 --> 04:31.603
<i>Sawchuk?</i>

04:31.605 --> 04:33.905
Jeez.

04:35.042 --> 04:38.610
Why don't you ask me
something a little easier?

04:38.612 --> 04:39.978
Hm?

04:41.615 --> 04:44.416
You gotta stay
low, stay forward;

04:44.418 --> 04:47.786
see the shot before
it leaves the stick.

04:57.364 --> 04:58.630
Come.

04:58.632 --> 05:00.666
Nah. Don't let
that dog in this house!

05:00.668 --> 05:01.700
She's not having
puppies in here.

05:01.702 --> 05:03.435
- But...

05:26.927 --> 05:30.662
I'm taking Mitch
with me to the plant.

05:33.067 --> 05:35.100
- Louis, Bob say he has
scouts coming to look at him

05:35.102 --> 05:36.535
any day now.

05:36.536 --> 05:37.969
- Yeah and this winter
we'll burn the floorboards

05:37.971 --> 05:39.871
to stay alive.

05:41.508 --> 05:42.674
- Take Terry.

05:42.676 --> 05:44.843
- Boys'll crucify Terry.

05:44.845 --> 05:47.112
- Why? What do you mean?

05:50.651 --> 05:52.884
- I mean I need Mitch.

05:57.858 --> 06:01.727
- Who's going to take care
of that cord of wood, huh?

06:11.372 --> 06:13.138
- Lady?

06:22.783 --> 06:24.416
Lady?

06:28.756 --> 06:30.489
Come on, girl. What's wrong?

06:33.694 --> 06:36.161
You're okay. You're just frozen.

06:36.163 --> 06:37.396
<i> You're gonna wake up.</i>

06:37.398 --> 06:39.531
<i> Come on!</i>

06:39.533 --> 06:42.768
<i> Just frozen. Please, come on.</i>

06:42.936 --> 06:45.904
<i> Breathe, breathe.</i>
<i> Come on. Come on.</i>

06:45.906 --> 06:47.973
- Terry?
- Come on.

06:47.975 --> 06:50.409
- What are you doing?

06:50.411 --> 06:51.743
<i> - They're okay.</i>

06:51.745 --> 06:54.079
<i> They're just frozen.</i>

06:54.081 --> 06:55.881
<i> They're gonna wake up!</i>

07:01.488 --> 07:03.054
No!

07:04.491 --> 07:06.758
- They're dead and
a good thing, too.

07:06.760 --> 07:09.594
We would'a had to drown 'em.

07:09.596 --> 07:11.563
- Huh.

07:11.564 --> 07:13.531
- Now, get 'em out of here
before your mother sees 'em.

07:16.036 --> 07:18.203
<i>Think God</i>
<i> lets dogs in heaven?</i>

07:18.205 --> 07:20.038
<i>If heaven doesn't</i>
<i> have pups running around,</i>

07:20.040 --> 07:21.606
<i> I don't wanna go there.</i>

07:23.076 --> 07:25.911
- In heaven, I'll be
as good a goalie as you.

07:25.913 --> 07:27.846
- You think too much, Terry.

07:27.848 --> 07:30.048
All you have to do
is stop the puck.

07:30.050 --> 07:32.184
Stay low and stay forward.

07:32.186 --> 07:33.686
Like last night.

07:33.687 --> 07:35.187
<i> Jimmy Day's coming</i>
<i> at me at full speed</i>

07:35.189 --> 07:37.088
<i> and lets fly a shot</i>

07:37.090 --> 07:38.557
and it's a 100 miles an hour,

07:38.559 --> 07:40.225
definitely close to
that, and I'm thinking

07:40.227 --> 07:42.361
stay low, stay forward

07:42.362 --> 07:44.496
and I see it before
he lets the shot fly.

07:44.498 --> 07:46.131
<i> And it's a bullet.</i>
It's in the glove.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.599
No rebound.

07:47.600 --> 07:49.066
You should've seen his
face! He thought he had me

07:49.069 --> 07:51.136
and that'll teach him
to bring his girl to a game.

07:51.138 --> 07:52.838
I feel bad for him.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.639
Who wants a soda?

07:54.641 --> 07:55.640
Ah...

08:00.948 --> 08:02.647
- Hey.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.518
Mitch?

08:08.655 --> 08:09.821
Mitch?

08:09.823 --> 08:12.524
<i> Aw, get in the swing.</i>

08:18.632 --> 08:20.799
- Kettleman says the body's
gonna stay in storage

08:20.801 --> 08:22.701
until the ground thaws.

08:29.142 --> 08:31.009
Stop it.

08:57.771 --> 08:59.638
<i>There's</i>
<i> something like a question</i>

08:59.640 --> 09:00.939
<i> in the air</i>

09:00.941 --> 09:03.875
<i> that will linger from now on.</i>

09:03.877 --> 09:05.810
"Take Terry.

09:05.812 --> 09:07.312
<i> I need Mitch."</i>

09:35.208 --> 09:38.076
<i>Dad! Dad!</i>

09:40.714 --> 09:42.280
Dad!

10:00.601 --> 10:03.268
<i>- All those nights</i>
<i>- I'd hear him in his sleep.</i>

10:03.270 --> 10:04.970
- Ah!

10:04.971 --> 10:06.671
<i>Stay low.</i>
<i> Stay forward.</i>

10:06.673 --> 10:08.673
<i> Forget the names they sing</i>
<i> at you through the screen.</i>

10:08.675 --> 10:10.075
- Ah!

10:10.077 --> 10:12.177
<i> Such preparedness.</i>

10:12.179 --> 10:14.012
<i> I'd lie awake and think.</i>

10:14.014 --> 10:15.780
- Ah!

10:18.185 --> 10:20.619
<i>And so</i>
<i> I got accustomed to the view</i>

10:20.621 --> 10:21.753
<i> from here.</i>

10:24.324 --> 10:26.725
<i> You watch them come</i>
<i> at you in waves.</i>

10:27.294 --> 10:28.393
<i> You watch 'em fly away.</i>

10:28.395 --> 10:30.245
<i>Go, go, go!</i>

10:30.246 --> 10:32.096
<i>A brief</i>
<i> flicker of relief</i>

10:32.099 --> 10:33.365
<i> but they'll be back.</i>

10:33.367 --> 10:37.302
<i> To knock on the gate</i>
<i> one more time.</i>

10:37.304 --> 10:39.237
<i> I could leave.</i>

10:39.239 --> 10:41.373
<i> But where would I go?</i>

10:42.743 --> 10:45.877
<i> This is my only home.</i>

10:48.081 --> 10:50.649
- Bob! Jack Adams.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.721
Listen, about that goalie
you're hiding up there

10:56.723 --> 10:58.990
in the frozen north,
I'm hearing good things.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.659
Suit him up with the
Spitfires, will ya'?

11:00.661 --> 11:03.028
Time to see what young
Mr. Sawchuk can do.

11:03.030 --> 11:04.729
<i>- Okay. Yeah.</i>
- Yeah, yeah.

11:04.731 --> 11:07.065
<i> - Well, I'll certainly</i>
<i> get onto that.</i>

11:07.067 --> 11:08.833
- Lil!

11:08.835 --> 11:11.903
Is there no way to make
this water a bit hotter?

11:12.673 --> 11:15.040
<i>All aboard!</i>

11:17.778 --> 11:20.445
- We'll be doing without
'cause I'm giving that to you.

11:20.947 --> 11:24.082
Think about that before
you piss it all away.

11:25.152 --> 11:28.319
- I'm gonna turn this
into bags of money, Mom.

11:28.321 --> 11:31.356
I'm going to send it all
back home on this very train.

11:31.358 --> 11:33.725
<i> - Don't be proud.</i>

11:35.195 --> 11:36.795
Uh...

11:36.797 --> 11:38.363
Go on.

11:38.365 --> 11:41.366
You'd miss your train standing
a foot away from it, you would.

11:51.945 --> 11:53.778
<i>For my money,</i>

11:53.780 --> 11:55.947
<i> Jack Adams</i>
<i> wanted to bring Terry</i>

11:55.949 --> 11:58.817
<i> down to Windsor to get</i>
<i> a glimpse across the river</i>

11:58.819 --> 12:01.319
at the Detroit skyline.

12:06.860 --> 12:10.195
Because he was known
to do things like that.

12:10.197 --> 12:12.097
They say he did the
same thing to Harry Lumley

12:12.099 --> 12:13.131
a few years earlier.

12:13.133 --> 12:14.165
<i> At the time,</i>

12:14.167 --> 12:16.801
teams had only one goalie

12:16.803 --> 12:18.937
One sweater per team.

12:18.939 --> 12:22.373
Detroit had Lumley and he'd
just won them the Stanley Cup.

12:23.376 --> 12:25.176
<i> - Hey, Burnsie, Burnsie!</i>

12:25.178 --> 12:28.079
- No one shuts the
door like this man!

12:29.216 --> 12:32.217
No one shuts
the door like Lumley!

12:36.857 --> 12:39.824
- Mr. Adams! You had a lot of
skeptics questioning how you

12:39.826 --> 12:41.059
<i>put the team together this year.</i>

12:41.061 --> 12:42.227
Bet you felt the pressure.

12:42.229 --> 12:44.929
Bet ya' feel like
a clever dog now!

12:47.968 --> 12:50.869
- I'm not the one
out there on the ice.

13:05.152 --> 13:08.820
Sometimes the sports desk
gets it right.

13:10.991 --> 13:13.124
I am the clever dog.

13:14.795 --> 13:16.327
<i>Harry Lumley</i>
<i> has traded his goalie stick</i>

13:16.329 --> 13:18.897
<i> for a pair of crutches</i>
<i> tonight. He'll be okay.</i>

13:18.899 --> 13:21.366
<i> The question is</i>
<i> will Detroit be okay?</i>

13:21.368 --> 13:23.334
<i> We're hearing good things</i>
<i> about this kid from Winnipeg,</i>

13:23.336 --> 13:24.536
<i> Terry Sawchuk.</i>

13:28.441 --> 13:30.275
<i>Hey, Lumley!</i>

13:30.277 --> 13:32.811
His head's too
big for your sweater.

13:34.381 --> 13:36.114
- Hope you figure that out
before you get in front

13:36.116 --> 13:37.849
<i> of the net, kid.</i>

13:40.453 --> 13:43.555
- Lumley, you're like his mom.

13:43.557 --> 13:46.524
- You get that first shot,
kid, you'll be fine.

13:46.526 --> 13:48.159
Yep, there he is.

13:48.161 --> 13:50.862
Who's game you
gonna play today, son?

13:52.499 --> 13:54.566
- Yours.
- Yours.

13:55.468 --> 13:57.335
- Mine.

13:57.336 --> 13:59.203
At our level,
right off the top.

13:59.206 --> 14:02.006
We're gonna grind these
sons of bitches down, boys!

14:02.008 --> 14:04.008
Let's go, Red Wings. Let's go!

14:04.010 --> 14:05.143
- Open the door!

14:05.145 --> 14:06.377
<i>There we go.</i>

14:06.379 --> 14:08.880
<i>Goalie goes first!</i>

14:08.882 --> 14:10.215
<i>Hup!</i>

14:12.152 --> 14:13.284
<i>Go!</i>

14:25.398 --> 14:26.531
<i>Up, up, up!</i>

14:31.471 --> 14:33.805
<i>Huh.</i>

14:33.806 --> 14:36.140
<i> It seems Mr. Sawchuk</i>
<i> has a style all his own.</i>

14:43.516 --> 14:45.917
<i> Boston scores!</i>

14:46.920 --> 14:48.052
- You paid three large for him?

14:48.054 --> 14:50.321
- I got it down to
two in the end. Yes.

14:50.323 --> 14:52.891
- Well, I don't see
what all the fuss is about.

14:52.893 --> 14:55.894
- I promise not to tell anyone
you said that.

14:55.896 --> 14:57.528
<i>Don't trade</i>
<i> Lumley yet!</i>

14:57.530 --> 14:59.998
<i>The whiz</i>
<i> kid misses the first shot.</i>

15:00.000 --> 15:04.102
<i> He's really got to look at</i>
<i> his stance in the net there.</i>

15:04.971 --> 15:07.005
- Okay, now listen, kid:

15:07.007 --> 15:09.574
this is no different
from the minors. All right?

15:09.576 --> 15:12.911
Just bigger pay cheques
and better women.

15:12.913 --> 15:15.680
You like women, don't ya'?

15:20.086 --> 15:21.286
- Yeah.

15:21.288 --> 15:23.521
- It's like if
we were brothers.

15:44.577 --> 15:46.110
<i>Yup, yup.</i>

15:48.014 --> 15:50.515
<i> Boston's got the puck.</i>

15:50.517 --> 15:53.184
<i> They're on the attack again.</i>

15:53.186 --> 15:55.353
<i> Ferguson shoots.</i>
<i> Sawchuk stops the puck!</i>

16:07.467 --> 16:10.201
- Yeah, they had a few, uh,
a few chances in the third.

16:10.203 --> 16:12.704
Uh, but we kept in it.

16:12.706 --> 16:15.606
<i> The players up here, they</i>
<i>don't try the same trick twice.</i>

16:15.608 --> 16:17.542
I learned that much.

16:17.544 --> 16:19.344
But, uh, mistakes like that,

16:19.346 --> 16:20.979
they cost me a
couple goals tonight

16:20.981 --> 16:23.114
and I won't let the same
thing happen on Wednesday.

16:26.686 --> 16:28.753
Oh, uh, either one
of you have a nickel

16:28.755 --> 16:31.289
so I could call
my mom?

16:34.127 --> 16:36.995
<i> Holy</i>
<i> Shinola,</i> Louis.

16:36.997 --> 16:38.997
You better listen to this!

16:40.667 --> 16:42.467
<i> In hockey news,</i>

16:42.469 --> 16:44.769
<i> Detroit Red Wings goalie</i>
<i> Harry Lumley has been traded</i>

16:44.771 --> 16:46.504
<i> to the Chicago Blackhawks.</i>

16:46.506 --> 16:48.206
Shit.

16:48.208 --> 16:49.540
<i> Yeah, I'm shocked.</i>

16:49.542 --> 16:51.242
<i> Uh, I had no idea.</i>

16:51.244 --> 16:53.311
<i> We just won the Cup.</i>
<i> But, as they say,</i>

16:53.313 --> 16:55.680
<i>who buys a house in Detroit with</i>
<i> Adams running the show, right?</i>

16:55.682 --> 16:57.615
<i>Trader Jack is showing his hand.</i>

16:57.617 --> 17:00.151
<i> It'll be his farm team</i>
<i> phenom, Terry Sawchuk,</i>

17:00.153 --> 17:02.387
<i> leading the team</i>
<i> come training camp time.</i>

17:06.259 --> 17:07.658
<i> ♪ So I'm telling me ♪</i>

17:07.660 --> 17:09.327
<i> ♪ to pack my bags ♪</i>

17:09.329 --> 17:11.029
<i> ♪ It's time for moving on ♪</i>

17:11.031 --> 17:13.131
<i> ♪ I'm bound to</i>
<i> do some reveling ♪</i>

17:13.133 --> 17:16.034
<i> ♪ It's time to travel on. ♪</i>

17:27.647 --> 17:29.480
- Can I help you, Sir?

17:29.482 --> 17:31.149
<i>Um...</i>

17:33.787 --> 17:35.486
No. Sorry.

17:35.488 --> 17:36.587
- Wait a minute.

17:36.589 --> 17:38.056
You're Detroit's new goalie.

17:38.058 --> 17:40.491
-<i> And so he is.</i>
Mr. Terry Sawchuk.

17:40.493 --> 17:42.627
We got royalty in here.

17:42.629 --> 17:45.396
- Can I get an
autograph for my son?

17:45.398 --> 17:48.132
- Uh... Sure.

17:49.502 --> 17:51.469
Uh...

17:51.471 --> 17:54.138
- Saw something you
liked in the window?

17:54.140 --> 17:56.174
- No. I, uh...

17:56.176 --> 17:57.341
I can't afford 'em.

17:57.343 --> 17:59.110
- Now, they pay
you, don't they?

17:59.646 --> 18:01.546
- What? Uh, yeah.

18:01.548 --> 18:03.614
But then I pay my landlord

18:03.616 --> 18:05.383
and then the rest
goes to my parents.

18:06.186 --> 18:08.152
- Good man.

18:08.388 --> 18:09.687
But you're going to
have to look sharp

18:09.689 --> 18:11.756
<i> now that you're</i>
<i> representing Detroit.</i>

18:11.758 --> 18:14.158
<i> I'll let you pay</i> two dollars
a week, no interest.

18:14.160 --> 18:15.660
You'll have 'em
paid off by January.

18:15.662 --> 18:17.612
- Janu-? Well,

18:17.613 --> 18:19.563
they won't do me much good
in the dead of winter.

18:19.566 --> 18:21.833
- Nonsense. You wear
them out today.

18:21.835 --> 18:24.202
- You'd let me do that?

18:24.204 --> 18:26.270
- If you stiff me, I know
where to find you, don't I?

18:26.272 --> 18:27.772
- Stopping those
dirty French pucks!

18:27.774 --> 18:30.775
- Yeah. I, uh...

18:30.777 --> 18:32.810
Yeah. I sure hope so.

18:32.812 --> 18:35.079
- Now, son:

18:35.080 --> 18:37.347
in Detroit we expect you to
bring more than just hope.

18:41.354 --> 18:43.688
- I'll try 'em on.
- All right, all right.

18:43.690 --> 18:45.123
- Thank you.

18:45.125 --> 18:46.591
Nice to meet you.

18:46.593 --> 18:48.426
- Nice to meet you, Terry.

18:58.238 --> 19:00.438
Fancy shoes.

19:22.829 --> 19:25.696
Making me work
for my tips today.

19:26.599 --> 19:29.333
- I gotta break in
these shoes, I guess.

19:29.335 --> 19:30.902
- Hm.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.506
- Stew, huh?

19:35.508 --> 19:37.275
Is that going to be
as good as my mother's

19:37.277 --> 19:38.709
Ukrainian dumplings?

19:38.711 --> 19:40.912
- I don't think I can
serve you in here.

19:41.748 --> 19:43.214
- Well, why not?

19:43.216 --> 19:44.782
- You look like
a hockey player.

19:44.784 --> 19:45.917
- I am.

19:45.919 --> 19:47.385
- Well, if you played
for Detroit,

19:47.387 --> 19:48.352
I'd have noticed you before.

19:48.354 --> 19:49.854
- I'm Detroit's new goalie.

19:50.323 --> 19:51.956
- Hm.

19:51.958 --> 19:54.258
Then I guess I'll serve you.

19:54.260 --> 19:56.594
I just won't
get too attached.

19:57.664 --> 20:00.331
As for the dumplings,
I've never tried 'em.

20:00.333 --> 20:03.301
But I bring 'em home to Bobby
some nights and he's a big fan.

20:06.472 --> 20:09.540
Stew like his Mama's.

20:25.692 --> 20:27.425
<i> The Montreal-Detroit rivalry</i>

20:27.427 --> 20:29.227
<i> is as heated as ever.</i>

20:29.229 --> 20:31.696
<i> That one goes all the way up</i>
<i> to the front offices of the</i>

20:31.698 --> 20:34.332
<i> Detroit General Manager,</i>
<i> Jack Adams</i>

20:34.334 --> 20:36.534
<i> and Montreal's Frank Selke.</i>

20:44.911 --> 20:47.845
<i>The score is tied three to three</i>
<i>with seconds left on the clock.</i>

20:54.887 --> 20:56.487
<i>It's in! The ref calls it a goal</i>

20:56.489 --> 20:58.489
<i> and Montreal ekes out a win</i>

20:58.491 --> 21:00.558
<i> with Detroit</i>
<i> nipping at their heels.</i>

21:10.737 --> 21:13.404
<i> Montreal still</i>
<i> holds the better record</i>

21:13.406 --> 21:15.706
<i> and no one hates losing</i>
<i> more than Jack Adams.</i>

21:16.876 --> 21:19.610
<i> Ha-ha-ha.</i>
<i> Take 'er easy, Jack!</i>

21:19.612 --> 21:22.580
<i> A ways to go before spring.</i>

21:22.915 --> 21:26.350
- Lil! The radio's fallen.

21:29.756 --> 21:30.888
Hey!

21:30.890 --> 21:33.057
What are you so
happy about? We lost.

21:33.059 --> 21:34.625
- I know, but I have

21:34.627 --> 21:36.694
a special friend
supposed to visit me tonight.

21:36.696 --> 21:37.928
- Oh, yeah? What's his name?

21:37.930 --> 21:39.563
That's his name.

21:39.565 --> 21:41.966
- Hey! Uncle.

21:41.968 --> 21:43.668
<i> Hey, don't mind Boiter.</i>

21:43.670 --> 21:46.037
He's gotta touch
every player after a game.

21:52.979 --> 21:54.929
- Whoa-whoa-whoa!

21:54.930 --> 21:56.880
Gordie says if you want to touch
him, it's gotta be his balls.

21:56.883 --> 21:59.050
- Get off me!
- Come on, come on!

21:59.052 --> 22:00.951
<i>- Get off me!</i>
<i>- Cool down.</i>

22:00.953 --> 22:02.386
- Hey, uh, snappy shoes!

22:02.388 --> 22:03.821
- Oh, yeah.

22:03.823 --> 22:05.389
- You must've
shelled out for 'em.

22:08.027 --> 22:09.994
<i>- Oop. Maybe pull it?</i>
<i>- Come on; little pull.</i>

22:09.996 --> 22:11.412
<i> Yeah, pull it,</i>
<i> pull hard. Harder.</i>

22:11.413 --> 22:12.829
<i> Come on. There you go.</i>
<i> That's it. That's it.</i>

22:12.832 --> 22:14.432
- Whoever did this
is paying for it!

22:14.434 --> 22:16.767
- C'mon, Terry. It's just fun.

22:41.794 --> 22:43.994
- So, how are you
settling in with the boys?

22:51.971 --> 22:53.504
There you go, son.

22:53.506 --> 22:55.639
- Thank you.

22:55.641 --> 22:57.375
- There won't be
anything in your life

22:57.377 --> 23:00.111
after like belonging to a team.

23:00.113 --> 23:02.980
Take it from a
land of experience.

23:02.982 --> 23:05.883
<i> No. Where does this sort</i>
<i> of sacrifice</i>

23:05.885 --> 23:08.853
<i> and loyalty</i>
<i> exist anymore, right?</i>

23:09.622 --> 23:11.922
Nah. It's an ancient game

23:11.924 --> 23:14.058
with ancient laws.

23:14.060 --> 23:16.761
But, God, I love it.

23:17.964 --> 23:20.931
Mm. Going to have to get you
some new shoes, I see.

23:20.933 --> 23:24.068
The fellas got a bit
of a sense of humour there.

23:24.771 --> 23:27.571
- Oh, no. Mr. Adams, I--

23:27.573 --> 23:29.774
- Mr. Sawchuk, if there's
one thing I know in this world

23:29.776 --> 23:31.075
to be true:

23:31.077 --> 23:33.644
you are worth the investment.

23:39.485 --> 23:40.651
- Thank you.

23:40.653 --> 23:41.886
- Please.

23:43.856 --> 23:46.824
Oh, that really
is nice on the toes.

23:47.026 --> 23:48.626
- Yeah?

23:49.895 --> 23:51.161
Pronovost, tough
as a bag of batteries.

23:51.164 --> 23:52.963
He gets the puck to me,
I see Delvecchio open...

23:52.965 --> 23:54.999
- You get a chance,
you gotta make the best of it.

23:55.001 --> 23:56.901
- Of course.
- And then Sawchuk.

23:56.903 --> 23:58.669
<i>Yeah. Then</i>
<i> Terry with the save.</i>

23:58.671 --> 23:59.971
- Mm.

23:59.972 --> 24:01.272
Sawchuk,
tonight, it was like...

24:01.273 --> 24:02.573
Hey!

24:02.575 --> 24:03.974
Great game.

24:06.012 --> 24:07.729
<i>Speech.</i>

24:07.730 --> 24:09.447
<i>- Yeah.</i>
<i>- Speech, speech!</i>

24:09.449 --> 24:11.215
<i>Uh,</i>

24:11.217 --> 24:13.684
I thought it was a
team effort. Um...

24:13.686 --> 24:15.553
I thought we really took
it to 'em tonight,

24:15.555 --> 24:17.188
we played a full 60 minutes

24:17.190 --> 24:18.956
and, uh,

24:18.958 --> 24:20.958
I'm really looking forward to
the playoffs, that's for sure.

24:20.960 --> 24:22.710
<i>Yeah.</i>

24:22.711 --> 24:24.461
- Mr. Sawchuk, everyone's
saying you got the skills

24:24.464 --> 24:26.797
to become one of the
greatest goalies in history.

24:33.072 --> 24:34.655
- Thank you.

24:34.656 --> 24:36.239
<i>- In my experience...</i>
<i>- That's it.</i>

24:36.242 --> 24:37.842
<i>Good game.</i>

24:39.712 --> 24:41.979
- Get a load
of all that, huh?

24:43.149 --> 24:44.982
Everybody loves a winner.

24:46.919 --> 24:49.620
I need eight more
of them to get the cup.

24:49.622 --> 24:52.590
<i> Can you get me eight wins?</i>

24:53.926 --> 24:55.125
- Okay.

24:55.127 --> 24:56.994
- All right.

25:02.201 --> 25:03.767
- Ah!
- Jesus! Oi!

25:14.614 --> 25:16.264
Ahh!

25:16.265 --> 25:17.915
<i> Amazing save by Sawchuk!</i>

25:17.917 --> 25:20.584
<i> Detroit is one period</i>
<i> away from sweeping Toronto</i>

25:20.586 --> 25:22.686
<i> out of the playoffs.</i>

25:22.688 --> 25:24.889
<i> A date with Montreal</i>
<i> within reach!</i>

25:26.626 --> 25:27.925
<i>Jesus! Holy cow.</i>

25:27.927 --> 25:29.126
- How's he doing?
We need this one.

25:29.128 --> 25:30.861
- No, Jack. It's
his elbow again.

25:30.863 --> 25:32.213
The doc says he needs surgery.

25:32.214 --> 25:33.564
- Surgery? Get off him.
- Yeah.

25:33.566 --> 25:34.999
How you feelin', son?

25:35.001 --> 25:36.768
Huh?

25:36.769 --> 25:38.536
Look at that face.
Tough as nails.

25:38.538 --> 25:40.571
I knew it the first
time I set eyes on him.

25:40.573 --> 25:42.973
You need this one, Jack.
Toughness! Heart!

25:42.975 --> 25:44.775
This is your man, I said.

25:44.777 --> 25:47.044
- If he goes out there,
it's not gonna heal proper.

25:47.046 --> 25:48.779
- You know they popped
out his eye one time

25:48.781 --> 25:50.180
when he played in the minors?

25:50.182 --> 25:51.982
Took a stick blade
right to the eye.

25:51.984 --> 25:54.685
They just patched it up
and popped it back in.

25:54.687 --> 25:57.087
<i> No. Someone plays</i>
<i> with that kind of heart</i>

25:57.089 --> 25:59.256
and that kind of
sacrifice for his team?

25:59.258 --> 26:02.026
That's someone that you
do not send to the hospital

26:02.028 --> 26:03.627
unless he says he needs to go!

26:03.629 --> 26:04.328
Huh? You ready to play.

26:04.330 --> 26:05.696
- Yeah, I'm good. I'm good.

26:05.698 --> 26:07.248
- You ready to
win this game?

26:07.249 --> 26:08.799
- I can go back in. I'm good.

26:08.801 --> 26:10.301
<i>Let's go. Let's go!</i>
<i> Let's go! All right!</i>

26:10.303 --> 26:11.686
- Ha. Hoo.

26:11.687 --> 26:13.070
<i>Upsy-doodle. Yeah.</i>

26:13.072 --> 26:15.139
<i> You wish you had</i>
<i> this kind of heart!</i>

26:15.141 --> 26:17.008
Okay.

26:17.009 --> 26:18.876
<i>Out on the ice,</i>
<i> with the game on the line,</i>

26:18.878 --> 26:20.878
<i> that's where I was alive.</i>

26:20.880 --> 26:23.614
<i> When you saw those words</i>
<i> up over the arena doors</i>

26:23.616 --> 26:25.182
<i> "Hockey tonight",</i>

26:25.184 --> 26:28.586
<i> man, they picked up your step.</i>

26:28.588 --> 26:30.354
<i> They told you life was good,</i>
<i> the woman with you</i>

26:30.356 --> 26:32.089
<i> was just the right woman,</i>

26:32.091 --> 26:34.758
<i>whichever joint you were heading</i>
<i> for was just the place to be</i>

26:34.760 --> 26:36.193
<i> before the game.</i>

26:36.195 --> 26:37.995
<i> Detroit leaves Montreal</i>

26:37.997 --> 26:41.231
<i>after taking the first two games</i>
<i> of the Stanley Cup finals!</i>

26:41.233 --> 26:43.634
- That's three games
in the books, boys.

26:43.636 --> 26:45.369
We got Montreal
on their heels.

26:45.371 --> 26:47.905
But I'll tell ya': the game
that ends a team's season

26:47.907 --> 26:50.240
is the hardest
one to win. Yeah.

26:50.242 --> 26:52.009
They're against the
ropes. Gettin' desperate.

26:52.011 --> 26:53.911
<i>- Yeah.</i>
- Where's Terry?

26:53.913 --> 26:56.280
- Mmm. I-I think-

26:56.282 --> 26:58.382
I think he left.

26:58.384 --> 27:00.184
- It's not a joke.
Where is he?

27:00.186 --> 27:02.186
- Didn't he, uh, didn't he
mention getting a haircut?

27:02.188 --> 27:03.954
- No, no. I think he
talked about, like,

27:03.956 --> 27:05.422
an ingrown toenail or something.

27:05.423 --> 27:06.889
- Ingrown toenail.
- Yeah. I think...

27:06.892 --> 27:09.293
- It's not funny, you guys!

27:09.295 --> 27:11.829
Fuck you guys!

27:11.831 --> 27:13.263
You know, it's on you too!

27:13.265 --> 27:15.666
I have a shit game,
we all have a shit game.

27:15.668 --> 27:16.767
- Yeah.

27:16.769 --> 27:18.335
- Right?
<i>- Right.</i>

27:18.336 --> 27:19.902
<i>- Can you read?</i>
<i>- Yeah, yeah.</i>

27:19.905 --> 27:23.307
- He better be in
the trainer's room.

27:25.945 --> 27:27.711
- Is he gone? Let's
get the fuck outta here.

27:27.713 --> 27:29.146
- Just be quiet, okay?
- Yeah.

27:29.148 --> 27:31.382
Come on. Go-go-go-go!

27:34.420 --> 27:36.120
<i>Terry. Quit it.</i>

27:36.122 --> 27:38.822
You're gonna burn a
hole right through her.

27:40.092 --> 27:41.692
- What? You like her?

27:41.694 --> 27:43.372
- No.
- Which one?

27:43.373 --> 27:45.051
- No. Marcel.
- Right there?

27:45.052 --> 27:46.730
- No, no, no, no. She has a
boyfriend, Bobby, or something.

27:47.900 --> 27:49.166
- Hey! Excuse me.

27:49.168 --> 27:51.669
Yeah. Please.

27:51.671 --> 27:53.837
- Hay is for horses.
<i>- Oh.</i>

27:53.839 --> 27:55.673
- Oh. Okay, uh...

27:55.675 --> 27:57.141
Pardonnez moi, Mademoiselle.

27:57.143 --> 27:59.710
But, um, may I bother
you for a second?

27:59.712 --> 28:01.245
Do you know who this is?

28:02.181 --> 28:04.381
You're looking at our
ticket to the top right there.

28:04.383 --> 28:05.282
- I'm working.

28:05.284 --> 28:06.917
- Okay, pardon me.

28:06.919 --> 28:09.420
We were just wondering if, um...

28:09.422 --> 28:11.355
Bobby's still
in the picture?

28:12.958 --> 28:14.925
- Bobby's still
in the picture.

28:14.927 --> 28:17.961
Only has three legs now
since the tractor ran over him.

28:17.963 --> 28:20.064
Thank you so
much for asking.

28:22.134 --> 28:24.334
Bobby's my dog.

28:25.237 --> 28:26.403
Okay. You're in!

28:26.405 --> 28:27.682
- I'm so sorry.
I don't know...

28:27.683 --> 28:28.960
<i>Okay.</i>
<i> So, he lives at...</i>

28:28.961 --> 28:30.238
- No, Marcel. No, I...
<i>- Yes.</i>

28:30.242 --> 28:31.809
He lives at
67 Military Road.

28:31.811 --> 28:32.876
- I-I...

28:34.780 --> 28:37.915
I do live there, though.

28:37.917 --> 28:40.150
Not with parents, or anything.

28:40.152 --> 28:41.785
- Wh-?

28:41.787 --> 28:44.788
No, no! Wait, wait, wait.
She's not even gonna...

28:46.258 --> 28:47.725
It's game over.
You're gonna have to jerk it.

28:47.727 --> 28:48.910
- You're a fuckin' idiot.

28:48.911 --> 28:50.094
That was smooth.

28:50.096 --> 28:51.729
- Yeah.
- Really smooth.

28:51.731 --> 28:52.996
- Good job.
- Yeah? Yeah?

28:52.998 --> 28:54.364
Very smooth.

29:22.161 --> 29:23.527
Asshole.

29:36.275 --> 29:39.042
- Let's go out there
and take it, boys.

29:39.044 --> 29:40.944
- It's our game tonight.

29:40.946 --> 29:43.547
- Full energy right
off the hop, boys.

29:43.549 --> 29:46.517
Gonna get to
our game: speed.

29:46.519 --> 29:48.185
You are going to
dump those pucks in deep.

29:48.187 --> 29:50.888
You will own
the neutral zone.

29:50.890 --> 29:52.556
No mercy.
No mercy.

29:52.558 --> 29:54.892
We will finish them off tonight.

29:54.894 --> 29:56.143
Who's ready?

29:56.144 --> 29:57.393
<i>Yeah. Yeah.</i>

29:57.396 --> 29:58.495
- Yeah?

29:58.497 --> 30:00.397
Ukey,

30:00.399 --> 30:02.566
you stand on your head all
season. Tonight any different?

30:02.568 --> 30:04.401
- No different.
- No different.

30:04.403 --> 30:06.470
Pronovost! Ready to make
their lives miserable?

30:06.472 --> 30:08.238
Yes. Yeah.

30:08.240 --> 30:09.573
- How are you feeling, son?

30:09.575 --> 30:11.141
- Good, sir. Good.

30:11.143 --> 30:12.576
- Gordie,

30:12.577 --> 30:14.010
you ready to take another
walk around this block?

30:14.013 --> 30:15.345
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah, yeah.

30:15.347 --> 30:16.847
- No matter what happens
in this building,

30:16.849 --> 30:19.016
you and I know,
we know the game is played

30:19.018 --> 30:20.317
between those
blood red posts.

30:20.319 --> 30:23.420
<i>All right, this is it.</i>
<i> Here we go.</i>

30:23.422 --> 30:26.857
<i> Nothin' else matters but</i>
<i> tonight, boys. Montreal?</i>

30:26.859 --> 30:29.326
<i> Montreal's got</i>
<i> nothin' on you!</i>

30:29.328 --> 30:31.595
Go, go!

30:36.101 --> 30:37.334
- Open the door.

30:37.336 --> 30:39.002
<i> Goalie goes first.</i>

30:46.011 --> 30:48.011
<i>You got the greatest goaltender</i>

30:48.013 --> 30:49.279
<i> in the league at one end.</i>

30:49.281 --> 30:51.348
<i> The kid. Sawchuk.</i>

30:51.350 --> 30:53.050
<i> Bearing down on him,</i>

30:53.052 --> 30:55.619
<i> the greatest goal scorer</i>
<i> in hockey history:</i>

30:55.621 --> 30:57.805
<i> Rocket Richard.</i>

30:57.806 --> 30:59.990
<i> This is one for the</i>
<i>history books, ladies and gents.</i>

30:59.992 --> 31:02.626
<i> Hold your families close.</i>
<i> Take the phone off the hook!</i>

31:02.628 --> 31:05.262
<i> Detroit could</i>
<i> win it all tonight.</i>

31:05.264 --> 31:08.899
<i>Welcome to the first elimination</i>
<i>game of the Stanley Cup finals!</i>

31:10.636 --> 31:13.503
<i>Out on the ice,</i>
<i> with the game on the line</i>

31:13.505 --> 31:15.305
<i> everyone depending on me.</i>

31:15.307 --> 31:17.541
<i> Half into an</i>
<i> animal crouch,</i>

31:17.543 --> 31:19.076
<i> like some poor bugger</i>

31:19.078 --> 31:21.879
<i> getting drilled</i>
<i> before a firing squad.</i>

31:23.449 --> 31:24.648
<i> Too late for last words.</i>

31:28.354 --> 31:29.353
Christ!

31:29.355 --> 31:30.954
- Dick, you gotta take it easy.

31:30.956 --> 31:32.990
- We've got three
times the shots on goal

31:32.992 --> 31:34.458
but it's three-nothing for them.

31:34.460 --> 31:35.993
How do you beat Sawchuk?

31:35.995 --> 31:37.394
He knows what you're
gonna do before you do it.

31:37.396 --> 31:39.429
I lie awake at night.

31:39.431 --> 31:41.932
I think my wife's
gonna leave me.

31:43.302 --> 31:46.136
- Coach, you in mid-stroke?

31:52.177 --> 31:55.646
- Harvey, what
the fuck was that?

31:55.648 --> 31:57.180
- Uh, that's an octopus.

31:57.182 --> 31:59.516
<i> - A what?</i>

31:59.518 --> 32:02.119
<i> Am I losing my damn mind?</i>

32:03.455 --> 32:05.155
<i>Eight legs.</i>

32:05.157 --> 32:07.124
Eight wins.

32:07.126 --> 32:08.992
Fuckers.

32:09.395 --> 32:12.229
We wanted it bad, yeah.

32:16.434 --> 32:18.234
But, uh, you know,
Terry was possessed.

32:18.237 --> 32:20.170
Oh,

32:20.172 --> 32:21.939
we tried to stay up, but...

32:21.941 --> 32:25.475
we knew crawling back
from a three-nil deficit

32:25.477 --> 32:28.512
with him in the
net was impossible.

32:29.982 --> 32:31.481
<i>Skate, skate, skate!</i>

32:37.656 --> 32:39.523
- What are you, nuts?
- I hate nuts.

32:40.259 --> 32:41.658
- Terry, I got it.

32:41.660 --> 32:44.394
Are you nuts? Huh?
Are you nuts?

32:44.396 --> 32:46.296
Huh?

32:46.298 --> 32:47.881
- Hey, Ref, you seen a
goddamn referee tonight?

32:47.882 --> 32:49.465
- All right, all right.
- Get back, Terry.

32:49.468 --> 32:52.135
- Good job, Marcel. Miss it.

33:05.651 --> 33:08.251
Ah!

33:14.426 --> 33:15.759
<i>... nine, eight,</i>

33:15.761 --> 33:19.129
<i> seven, six, five,</i>

33:19.131 --> 33:22.299
<i> four, three, two, one!</i>

33:27.072 --> 33:28.672
<i> Detroit wins the cup!</i>

33:40.152 --> 33:43.720
Here we go!
Oh! Oh-ho-ho-ho!

33:47.092 --> 33:49.393
Pretty intense for your first
NHL game, hey there, call-up?

33:49.395 --> 33:51.395
No. We're always
ready in Edmonton

33:51.397 --> 33:53.163
for when we
get our chance.

33:53.165 --> 33:54.798
- Who's good
up there, anyway?

33:54.800 --> 33:58.201
- Gotta see this goalie,
Glenn Hall.

33:58.203 --> 33:59.636
<i> Spreads like a butterfly.</i>

33:59.638 --> 34:01.605
<i> - Oh, hear that, Uke?</i>

34:01.607 --> 34:03.306
You better
watch your back;

34:03.308 --> 34:05.809
got a butterfly in the wings.

34:05.811 --> 34:08.445
- Okay. Here's the deal:

34:08.447 --> 34:10.380
<i> you're going to put chicken</i>
<i> bones in Boiter's hockey bag.</i>

