38:39.584 --> 38:41.451
they better
be damn genies.

38:43.055 --> 38:44.621
<i>Yeah, I got it.</i>

38:44.623 --> 38:46.923
<i>Yes, indeed.</i>

38:46.925 --> 38:49.859
<i>Go back for that.</i>

38:49.861 --> 38:51.094
<i> Come on, I'll pass you one.</i>

38:51.096 --> 38:52.529
- Terry Sawchuk.

38:52.531 --> 38:54.764
<i> - In the flesh.</i>

38:54.766 --> 38:57.600
- Flesh is right. He got fat.

38:57.602 --> 38:58.535
<i>Good job, ladies.</i>

39:00.439 --> 39:03.807
- I'll make damn sure
he burns it off, sir.

39:03.809 --> 39:05.742
- Yeah.

39:07.646 --> 39:09.846
<i>All right.</i>
<i> Let's go.</i>

39:11.383 --> 39:13.817
- Hey, Ter. Come on in.

39:15.354 --> 39:17.554
- Mr. Norris.
Nice to see you again.

39:17.556 --> 39:19.789
- How are you, Terry?
- Good. Good.

39:20.058 --> 39:22.892
- Uh, let's get you
on the scale, huh, son?

39:24.830 --> 39:27.497
Let's see
what we got here.

39:30.702 --> 39:32.869
All right. Up.

39:32.871 --> 39:34.571
Oh, boy.

39:35.740 --> 39:36.906
All right. Let's try this.

39:36.908 --> 39:38.491
- You know what?

39:38.492 --> 39:40.075
Let me try it again without
the cigarette in my hand.

39:40.078 --> 39:41.978
Yeah, sure.

39:41.980 --> 39:44.814
You spend the off-season
eating Ukrainian dumplings

39:44.816 --> 39:46.449
out of the Calder Trophy?

39:48.102 --> 39:49.752
Game time. You're going
to drop the weight.

39:49.755 --> 39:50.920
Right?

39:50.922 --> 39:52.455
The fans, they're fickle.

39:52.457 --> 39:54.057
They love you one night
and hate you the next.

39:54.059 --> 39:55.125
Let's not give them a reason.

39:55.127 --> 39:56.459
- I'll get the weight down.

39:56.461 --> 39:57.660
- All right.
- Okay.

39:57.662 --> 39:59.279
Good.

39:59.280 --> 40:00.897
Hit that door on your way out,
if you wouldn't mind.

40:05.570 --> 40:06.169
- Okay.

40:14.713 --> 40:15.912
- The football player.

40:15.914 --> 40:16.946
- Hockey.

40:17.582 --> 40:20.150
- I don't care
much for either.

40:20.152 --> 40:21.885
My Dad owns this
place so I fake it.

40:21.887 --> 40:23.753
Hockey's good for business.

40:23.755 --> 40:26.055
- Well, I'm a goalie.

40:26.057 --> 40:29.559
And the job of the goalie
is to stop the puck

40:29.561 --> 40:31.694
from going in

40:31.696 --> 40:33.530
the net.

40:36.802 --> 40:39.436
And when you do...

40:39.438 --> 40:41.571
you're the hero.

40:41.573 --> 40:43.540
When you don't,

40:44.876 --> 40:46.910
you come to the bar alone.

40:48.079 --> 40:50.713
- Looks like it
gets pretty rough.

40:51.483 --> 40:52.649
<i>Oh, oh, oh!</i>

40:52.651 --> 40:53.883
- Try that again, Merle,

40:53.885 --> 40:55.685
and I'll dig it into
the back of your skull!

40:58.190 --> 40:59.622
<i>Jeez.</i>

40:59.624 --> 41:01.958
Jesus! What
are you, part lion?

41:02.627 --> 41:05.562
- Maybe I should have a goalie
to stand right there between me

41:05.564 --> 41:08.064
- and all of them.
- You mean a defenseman.

41:08.066 --> 41:10.934
- I think I'd
rather a goalie.

41:14.039 --> 41:16.089
<i> You hungry?</i>

41:16.090 --> 41:18.140
Tonight's gravy's so
thick you could walk on it.

41:20.111 --> 41:21.678
- I'll just take a whiskey.

41:28.503 --> 41:30.153
<i> What's going on in Detroit?</i>

41:30.155 --> 41:33.022
<i> The Wings are not the same</i>
<i> team they were last year.</i>

41:39.097 --> 41:41.164
<i>Come on!</i>

41:41.166 --> 41:42.866
- Which team you
playing for, Marcel?

41:44.002 --> 41:44.968
- Detroit.

41:44.970 --> 41:47.136
<i>- You're hanging me out to dry!</i>

41:47.138 --> 41:49.072
Hanging me out to dry.

42:30.916 --> 42:32.682
- Huh.

42:34.219 --> 42:36.786
Feeling the need for
a drink after that one.

42:37.022 --> 42:40.089
- Naw, I, uh...

42:40.091 --> 42:42.625
No.

42:42.627 --> 42:44.561
- Yeah.

42:55.206 --> 42:57.340
- Fucker.

42:57.342 --> 42:59.609
Get out of here.

43:15.927 --> 43:18.761
<i>Christmas,</i>
<i> with his foot in a cast.</i>

43:18.763 --> 43:20.830
<i> That came off</i>

43:20.832 --> 43:22.865
and Pulford skated
over three of his fingers.

43:22.867 --> 43:25.268
Besides starving himself,

43:25.270 --> 43:28.605
cuts, bruises, disc
ruptures from that crouch,

43:28.607 --> 43:31.040
he was only sleeping
three hours a night.

43:31.042 --> 43:34.611
But he would've remembered what
happened when Lumley was out

43:34.613 --> 43:36.079
<i> with a broken ankle.</i>

43:36.681 --> 43:37.914
- Great. You're not
gonna believe this:

43:37.916 --> 43:39.482
Glenn Hall is in town
doing a hockey camp.

43:39.483 --> 43:41.049
Just left his hotel for the
airport. We're going to ...

43:41.052 --> 43:43.019
- No, No, No.
<i>- Catch him at the airport</i>

43:43.021 --> 43:44.437
- Forget the freeze.
Forget the freeze.

43:44.438 --> 43:45.854
Just stitch me up and
get me back out there.

43:45.857 --> 43:47.724
<i>- Have you seen your face?</i>
- Let him go.

43:47.726 --> 43:49.392
We're good here.
We're good here.

43:49.393 --> 43:51.059
- All right, forget it.
I guess we're good here.

43:51.062 --> 43:53.062
Stitch him up!

43:54.099 --> 43:55.765
- It's only a couple years
since they tossed him

43:55.767 --> 43:57.734
Lumley's sweater.

43:58.069 --> 43:59.836
Six goalies in the league.

43:59.838 --> 44:02.005
One sweater per team.

44:02.007 --> 44:04.841
With general managers
short on cotton and patience,

44:04.843 --> 44:07.377
we goalies were constantly
looking over our shoulders.

44:07.379 --> 44:09.379
<i>Sawchuk, Sawchuk,</i>
<i> Sawchuk, Sawchuk.</i>

44:13.318 --> 44:15.151
- You love me tonight, do ya'?

44:16.921 --> 44:18.921
Go fuck yourselves.

44:49.120 --> 44:51.354
- Hey. Hey, Terry.

45:01.833 --> 45:04.133
Come on, darlin'.

45:08.907 --> 45:10.940
Hey, let's go.

45:16.815 --> 45:18.431
- My jacket.
- Yeah.

45:18.432 --> 45:20.048
- My jacket.
- I got it. I got it.

45:20.051 --> 45:22.018
- Okay.

45:22.020 --> 45:23.119
Go to bed, honey.

45:23.121 --> 45:24.921
- Mm-hm.

45:26.791 --> 45:28.925
- I'm not drunk.

45:28.927 --> 45:31.394
I just, I didn't have dinner.

45:32.263 --> 45:33.963
- All right.

45:37.068 --> 45:38.968
<i>Detroit loses a fourth straight</i>

45:38.970 --> 45:41.871
<i>despite Sawchuk turning away an</i>
<i> unbelievable 48 shots on goal.</i>

45:41.873 --> 45:43.323
- Terry, what
were you thinking

45:43.324 --> 45:44.774
when you let that
easy one by in the third?

45:44.776 --> 45:46.743
- I don't know.
- Is the pressure

45:46.745 --> 45:48.511
to repeat the season you
had last year getting to you?

45:48.513 --> 45:50.847
- Why don't you get out there
and take 50 shots to the face?

45:50.849 --> 45:52.882
I'll ask how you
feel about it, okay?

45:52.884 --> 45:54.951
- Hey. Out.

46:01.426 --> 46:03.459
Where are we?

46:07.899 --> 46:10.967
Where are we!?

46:10.969 --> 46:12.034
- Detroit.

46:12.036 --> 46:14.237
<i> - No, you invalid.</i>

46:15.240 --> 46:17.173
Rock bottom!

46:17.175 --> 46:20.476
That's where we are!

46:20.478 --> 46:23.079
And you sorry sons of bitches
better figure out a way

46:23.081 --> 46:24.881
to climb out.

46:24.883 --> 46:28.050
Unless you wanna be playing
for Coal Mine Workers of America

46:28.052 --> 46:29.485
next season

46:29.487 --> 46:32.522
which is all
you'll be fit to do!

46:33.958 --> 46:35.892
And you:

46:36.461 --> 46:39.228
<i> not enjoying the</i>
pucks coming at ya'?

46:40.398 --> 46:42.265
Maybe you're not fit
for the job anymore.

46:42.267 --> 46:45.201
- We're out of
the playoffs anyway.

46:45.203 --> 46:46.869
- What did you say?

46:46.871 --> 46:48.437
- I said we're out of
the playoffs anyway.

46:48.439 --> 46:50.106
We got five games left.

46:50.108 --> 46:51.991
And they don't mean anything

46:51.992 --> 46:53.875
and I got these press jerkoffs
rubbing my face in shit.

46:53.878 --> 46:54.544
<i> - Yeah, yeah.</i>

46:54.546 --> 46:56.179
No. You don't want that.

46:56.181 --> 46:58.948
You don't want
shit in the face.

47:02.420 --> 47:04.120
Get down

47:04.122 --> 47:05.888
and shit on the floor.

47:11.462 --> 47:14.230
Shit on the floor!!

47:19.204 --> 47:21.604
You can't even
fucking do that right?

47:24.475 --> 47:26.375
I got no room

47:26.377 --> 47:28.377
on my hockey club

47:28.379 --> 47:31.614
for anyone who
can't take the heat.

47:55.373 --> 47:56.639
- Jack.

47:56.641 --> 47:58.941
Jack's a dumb name. Jack.

47:58.943 --> 48:00.643
It sounds like
a cat throwing up.

48:00.645 --> 48:01.944
- You wouldn't name a kid Jack?

48:01.946 --> 48:04.280
- Not on your life.

48:04.282 --> 48:06.916
Maybe... Penelope?

48:06.918 --> 48:08.351
- I like Anthony.

48:08.353 --> 48:09.585
- Mm.

48:09.587 --> 48:11.454
I had a regular
named Anthony.

48:11.456 --> 48:14.190
He always took his pants off
when he drank Canadian whiskey.

48:14.192 --> 48:16.092
- I bet when you name your
kid Anthony, you forget about

48:16.094 --> 48:17.526
all the Anthony's that
you didn't like before.

48:17.528 --> 48:20.463
- I didn't say
I didn't like him.

48:27.171 --> 48:30.273
You know, I always
liked the name Charles.

48:32.310 --> 48:34.911
- Chuck? Chuck?
Chuck Sawchuk?

48:36.114 --> 48:39.081
- Who says my babies
are gonna be Sawchuks?

48:40.018 --> 48:43.352
- Well, I'm not sittin' here

48:43.354 --> 48:45.655
coming up with baby names

48:45.657 --> 48:47.590
for you and
some other fella.

48:47.592 --> 48:50.993
- Mm. Wow. You
don't waste any time.

48:52.563 --> 48:54.664
- Take your
shot when you, uh...

48:55.934 --> 48:57.967
when you get the chance.

49:01.572 --> 49:04.707
But if Jack trades me, I'm
going to have to start all over

49:05.410 --> 49:08.411
with some Catholic girl
from Boston

49:08.413 --> 49:09.612
or a French girl
from Montreal.

49:09.614 --> 49:11.147
Oh, I hear they're spicy.

49:11.149 --> 49:13.082
- What kind of dad
would you be, anyway?

49:13.084 --> 49:14.317
Always on the
road. Never home.

49:14.319 --> 49:16.585
- No, no way. No way.

49:16.587 --> 49:19.956
I'd flood the yard,
make a rink.

49:20.458 --> 49:22.191
I'd teach 'em
all to play hockey.

49:22.193 --> 49:24.060
Have my own little
team of midgets.

49:24.062 --> 49:26.195
Bet on 'em. Retire.

49:35.306 --> 49:37.106
- Okay.

49:39.210 --> 49:41.210
- Okay?

49:42.213 --> 49:44.013
Oh...

49:44.015 --> 49:46.215
Okay? O-okay what?

49:46.217 --> 49:49.118
Okay. Okay, okay, what?

49:49.120 --> 49:50.753
Okay, you'd marry me?

49:51.289 --> 49:53.222
- If-if that's
what you're asking?

49:53.224 --> 49:54.557
- Well, yeah. It is now!

49:54.559 --> 49:56.225
- Well, then yeah!

50:03.001 --> 50:04.667
- What if I got hurt
and I couldn't play?

50:04.669 --> 50:06.235
- That's easy. I'd just

50:06.237 --> 50:07.770
leave you for
Merle the drunk.

50:07.772 --> 50:10.706
He's going to inherit a fortune
when his mother dies.

50:12.143 --> 50:16.712
I would live in a railway car
and beg for a living

50:17.548 --> 50:21.183
if it meant that I got to
do it with Mr. Terry Sawchuk.

50:24.522 --> 50:27.423
You just have to
promise me one thing:

50:27.425 --> 50:30.493
that every now and then you'll
take your mind off hockey.

50:34.198 --> 50:35.731
My mind's not on hockey now.

50:50.615 --> 50:52.181
<i>- Terry.</i>
- Hey.

50:52.183 --> 50:54.784
I, um...

50:54.786 --> 50:58.054
I'm sick about how
we went out this year.

50:58.790 --> 51:00.756
I let the pressure get to me.

51:01.726 --> 51:04.126
- Two years in a row
you win the Vezina trophy

51:04.128 --> 51:06.729
and all you think about
are the pucks that got in?

51:07.799 --> 51:08.597
- I'm getting married.

51:08.599 --> 51:10.466
- Well, congratulations.

51:10.467 --> 51:12.334
- Yeah, I know you said to
stay away from the girls,

51:12.336 --> 51:14.136
so I-I figured I'd
do it in the off season.

51:14.138 --> 51:15.688
- Oh, that's smart.

51:15.689 --> 51:17.239
- Yeah. But come fall,
I'll be focused on my game.

51:17.241 --> 51:19.141
- Good. Not worried about it.

51:19.143 --> 51:21.710
- Yeah. Just, uh, just
thinking about the future,

51:21.712 --> 51:23.446
you know?

51:23.448 --> 51:25.548
Um...

51:25.550 --> 51:28.851
Maybe buy a house. Just...

51:28.853 --> 51:30.719
Just not sure.

51:30.721 --> 51:32.555
- Hm.

51:32.557 --> 51:36.258
You and me, huh? Always in
the balance if we don't perform.

51:37.228 --> 51:40.429
I think of you
as a son, Terry.

51:40.431 --> 51:42.598
I expect to be
invited to that wedding.

51:49.874 --> 51:52.608
<i> A shot from the point...</i>

51:52.610 --> 51:55.478
<i> Sawchuk bats at it. Wait!</i>

51:56.614 --> 51:58.547
<i> He's down. He's hit.</i>

51:58.549 --> 52:01.450
<i> Sawchuk is down and</i>
<i> the puck is in the net!</i>

52:07.225 --> 52:08.491
- You all right?

52:08.493 --> 52:10.593
- You maybe see some,
ah, teeth around here,

52:10.595 --> 52:12.561
- would you, buddy?
<i>- You got it.</i>

52:12.563 --> 52:13.896
<i>Sawchuk!</i>

52:13.898 --> 52:15.865
<i> That goal light's</i>
<i> gonna give you a sunburn.</i>

52:15.867 --> 52:17.500
- What son of a
bitch said that?

52:17.502 --> 52:18.667
<i> That stuff</i>

52:18.669 --> 52:20.970
<i> doesn't bother these guys.</i>

52:20.971 --> 52:23.272
<i> Terry is a professional.</i>
<i> They just tune that stuff out.</i>

52:23.274 --> 52:25.541
- Right there.
<i>- Sawchuk. Sawchuk!</i>

52:26.511 --> 52:28.244
- Oh, no, no.

52:28.679 --> 52:30.496
- Yeah?

52:30.497 --> 52:32.314
<i>Not</i>
<i>sure that's the case this time!</i>

52:32.316 --> 52:33.782
- Tabernac! Oh, no, no!
Wait, wait, wait!

52:35.602 --> 52:37.419
<i>Do you want to</i>
<i> get in there, huh? Huh?</i>

52:37.421 --> 52:39.221
Do you want to get
in the fuckin' net?

52:39.223 --> 52:40.956
- No! No!

52:40.957 --> 52:42.690
- Get the fuck out! You
better run! You better run, boy!

52:45.863 --> 52:47.563
- Damn it!

52:49.433 --> 52:51.200
- I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

52:53.237 --> 52:54.870
- Fan hit a nerve
there, huh, Terry?

52:54.872 --> 52:56.805
- Okay, fellas, I could use...

52:56.807 --> 52:58.507
Give me a minute.
I'm in a little pain, here.

52:58.509 --> 53:00.276
- How do you think
kids who look up to you

53:00.278 --> 53:01.844
will feel about you
going after a fan?

53:01.846 --> 53:03.345
- Okay. Please, guys,
he asked for a minute.

53:03.347 --> 53:04.713
Just give him some space,
okay? Please, please.

53:04.715 --> 53:06.348
- Do you know
how many people

53:06.350 --> 53:07.483
would want to be
in your position?

53:07.485 --> 53:08.901
- Okay, come on.
That's enough!

53:08.902 --> 53:10.318
- I think this is
the first time in hockey

53:10.321 --> 53:11.687
we've seen someone crack
under pressure like--

53:11.689 --> 53:12.588
- That's enough! I said--

53:13.691 --> 53:15.324
What the fuck
are you doing?

53:15.326 --> 53:16.792
- It's okay. Calm down.

53:16.794 --> 53:19.361
- All right. Let's go, fellas.
You got enough, huh? Thanks.

53:19.363 --> 53:21.313
<i> You! What the hell?</i>
<i> It's not bad enough</i>

53:21.314 --> 53:23.264
<i> that in the supermarket</i>
<i> they're asking my wife,</i>

53:23.267 --> 53:25.634
"What the goddamn is the
matter with Terry Sawchuk?"

53:25.636 --> 53:27.236
Now, what are these guys
gonna write?

53:27.238 --> 53:28.437
How's it gonna look, huh?

53:28.438 --> 53:29.637
That the inmates are
<i> running the ship!</i>

53:29.640 --> 53:31.807
- I'm the one standin'
on my head out there!

53:31.809 --> 53:33.776
- Maybe you need to rest?

53:33.778 --> 53:35.628
- No.

53:35.629 --> 53:37.479
- Yeah. I'm calling
Glenn Hall up from Edmonton.

53:40.451 --> 53:42.101
- You know what?

53:42.102 --> 53:43.752
That pond hockey hick
won't last a fucking game!

53:56.901 --> 53:58.634
<i> Belliveau gets it up the ice</i>

53:58.636 --> 53:59.735
<i> to Geoffrion who shoots.</i>

53:59.737 --> 54:01.403
<i> Kicked away by Hall!</i>

54:01.405 --> 54:04.573
<i> This kid's coverage</i>
<i> is something else.</i>

54:04.575 --> 54:06.375
<i>- Terry, you hungry?</i>
- What?

54:06.377 --> 54:08.844
<i> - The Canadiens</i>
<i> are testing him tonight.</i>

54:08.846 --> 54:10.512
- Steak, salad, Jello.
All your favorites.

54:10.514 --> 54:11.914
- Goddammit, Pat!
I don't want any food

54:11.916 --> 54:12.948
next to the chesterfield. Shh!

54:12.950 --> 54:14.250
It's fine!

54:14.251 --> 54:15.551
<i> - Sawchuk's injury</i>
<i> seemed a real blow</i>

54:15.553 --> 54:17.920
<i> to the Wings fighting</i>
<i> for a playoff spot.</i>

54:17.922 --> 54:20.856
<i> But Hall's</i>
<i> proving himself nicely.</i>

54:20.858 --> 54:24.660
<i> Jack Adams must be</i>
<i> feeling relieved at that.</i>

54:24.662 --> 54:26.962
- He's gonna replace me.
- Hey.

54:26.964 --> 54:28.464
- He's going to replace me.

54:28.466 --> 54:29.898
- No.
- He's done with me.

54:29.900 --> 54:31.900
One day he's calling me
"son" and then the next day

54:31.902 --> 54:33.369
I'm out in the fucking cold!

54:33.371 --> 54:35.655
- You don't need him.

54:35.656 --> 54:37.940
- Jesus Christ, Pat!
I can't eat this fattening shit!

54:41.712 --> 54:43.579
<i> Another shot gloved by Hall--</i>

54:53.057 --> 54:55.591
- I, uh...

54:55.593 --> 54:57.826
I'm sorry.

54:58.996 --> 55:01.497
It's not you.

55:04.935 --> 55:07.970
You're the only good thing.

55:10.474 --> 55:12.775
- It's okay.

55:13.711 --> 55:16.812
I know this has been tough.

55:21.952 --> 55:24.586
- Six goalies in the league.

55:24.588 --> 55:26.922
One sweater per team.

55:26.924 --> 55:29.725
You're working paycheque
to paycheque.

55:29.727 --> 55:32.328
<i> You're barely scraping by.</i>

55:36.067 --> 55:38.033
<i>Yeah. The good old</i>

55:38.035 --> 55:39.635
hockey game.

55:39.637 --> 55:44.973
It'll ask for everything you got
and, in the end, it'll kill ya'.

55:44.975 --> 55:46.475
<i> Goalies first.</i>

55:46.477 --> 55:48.410
- Hey! Hey, can I get in there?

55:50.348 --> 55:53.048
<i>Read a catcher</i>

55:53.050 --> 55:55.684
in baseball once said:

55:55.686 --> 55:58.487
"There must be some reason

55:58.489 --> 56:01.390
we're the only ones
facing the other way."

56:01.392 --> 56:02.491
Hm.

56:02.893 --> 56:04.727
- Hey.

56:06.864 --> 56:09.832
It's like I'm holding God.

56:10.768 --> 56:12.701
Hi.

56:33.758 --> 56:37.493
- He would have thrown
himself in front of a bus

56:37.495 --> 56:39.762
for that team in
the first five years.

56:41.365 --> 56:42.965
<i> That's the kind</i>
<i> of goalie he was.</i>

56:42.966 --> 56:44.566
<i>That's right, Mr.</i>
<i> Terry Sawchuk has been traded</i>

56:44.568 --> 56:45.934
<i> from the Detroit Red Wings</i>
<i> to the Boston Bruins.</i>

56:45.936 --> 56:48.137
- Hello.

56:48.139 --> 56:49.972
- It's a boy.

56:49.974 --> 56:51.940
It's a boy.

56:53.944 --> 56:55.677
Well, I-I...

56:55.679 --> 56:57.479
Wonder how he's gonna
like living in Boston?

56:57.782 --> 56:59.581
- Boston?

56:59.583 --> 57:00.816
<i> - Just heard</i>
<i> it on the radio.</i>

57:00.818 --> 57:03.051
They traded
you to the Bruins.

57:54.472 --> 57:56.071
- Hey, pal.

57:56.073 --> 57:58.941
- My wife had a baby.

57:59.543 --> 58:02.244
- Yeah. I know that.

58:02.246 --> 58:04.480
<i> - Good.</i>

58:05.916 --> 58:07.549
- But know what?

58:07.551 --> 58:09.151
I think we
should go see her.

58:09.153 --> 58:11.186
Come on.
I'll drive ya'. Hm?

58:11.188 --> 58:13.589
- I think Jack
should meet him.

58:13.591 --> 58:15.691
- Okay, listen, man:

58:17.127 --> 58:19.261
it's two in the morning.

58:19.263 --> 58:21.830
Jack is not even
in the building.

58:23.601 --> 58:26.134
Come on. Let's go home.

58:26.136 --> 58:28.837
I'll drive you.

58:31.509 --> 58:32.941
Please. Get in the car.

58:32.943 --> 58:35.677
- No! Fuck the car!

58:36.780 --> 58:38.947
- Please?

58:39.683 --> 58:41.850
- He never even came
to the wedding.

58:43.187 --> 58:45.120
- Yeah, I know.

58:46.824 --> 58:49.057
Well, I did.

58:50.861 --> 58:53.262
I came to the wedding.

58:58.536 --> 59:01.003
Come on. Hm?

59:01.005 --> 59:03.572
Let's go home.

59:05.042 --> 59:06.808
- You had a name card, Jack!

59:06.810 --> 59:09.011
- Sh, sh, sh. Terry, listen:

59:11.148 --> 59:14.016
gonna be okay. Hm?

59:14.218 --> 59:16.952
- I'm going to
miss you, brother.

59:18.155 --> 59:21.089
- I'll miss you, too.

59:21.091 --> 59:23.625
Right now,
time to go to bed.

59:23.627 --> 59:25.193
- Mm. Okay.

59:25.195 --> 59:27.796
- That's it.
Okay. Follow me.

59:27.798 --> 59:30.332
<i>Go take a shower,</i>
<i> ya' bunch a fuckin' bums!</i>

59:30.334 --> 59:32.134
<i> Ya' need it!</i>

59:32.135 --> 59:33.935
- So, who gets
to kill that guy?

59:49.587 --> 59:51.853
Pathetic pouters.

59:52.823 --> 59:55.691
Pull your heads out of your
asses and compete out there!

59:55.693 --> 59:58.260
You're an embarrassment.

59:58.262 --> 1:00:00.195
We got Terry Sawchuk in goal!

1:00:00.197 --> 1:00:03.899
<i> We finally have a chance</i>
<i> to make the playoffs so just</i>

1:00:03.901 --> 1:00:05.767
<i> pull it together.</i>

1:00:07.871 --> 1:00:10.739
This is our barn.

1:00:10.741 --> 1:00:13.875
We let them walk
into our barn and piss

1:00:13.877 --> 1:00:15.644
all over our barn.

1:00:16.680 --> 1:00:19.114
Shit's spraying all over
our barn, boys, let me tell you.

1:00:21.318 --> 1:00:23.385
Who's going to
clean up that shit, huh?

1:00:23.387 --> 1:00:24.720
Hm?

1:00:24.722 --> 1:00:27.756
Our barn stinks like shit!

1:00:27.758 --> 1:00:29.992
And so do you!

1:00:39.803 --> 1:00:41.637
<i>See, guys?</i>

1:00:41.639 --> 1:00:43.905
This...

1:00:43.907 --> 1:00:46.642
This is the team
bonding we need! We're--

1:00:46.644 --> 1:00:49.645
We're brothers! This
is how it's supposed to be!

1:00:51.348 --> 1:00:53.181
<i> Come on, man.</i>

1:00:53.183 --> 1:00:55.817
Look, we're a team!

1:00:56.754 --> 1:00:58.253
Who's doing that?

1:01:00.124 --> 1:01:02.190
<i> Schmidt's right!</i>

1:01:02.192 --> 1:01:06.028
We could make the playoffs with
Terry backstopping us but we...

1:01:06.030 --> 1:01:08.330
We gotta bond.

1:01:08.332 --> 1:01:12.000
Cal's never been
on a roller coaster.

1:01:12.703 --> 1:01:15.804
Who's never been
on a roller coaster?

1:01:17.041 --> 1:01:19.207
Well, let's go to a bar!

1:01:19.209 --> 1:01:22.077
Hey? You guys
want to go to a bar?

1:01:23.947 --> 1:01:27.683
All right. Well,
let's hit the showers,

1:01:28.152 --> 1:01:30.252
and then we'll hit the town!

1:01:32.322 --> 1:01:33.822
Okay.

1:01:36.160 --> 1:01:38.694
- You want to come
for a drink, Terry?

1:01:38.696 --> 1:01:41.029
- Uh, maybe some other time.

1:01:43.701 --> 1:01:45.967
- All right.

1:01:47.938 --> 1:01:49.988
<i> We let Sawchuk go</i>

1:01:49.989 --> 1:01:52.039
<i> because we found ourselves</i>
<i> with two top goalies.</i>

1:01:52.042 --> 1:01:55.877
<i> Hall is more advanced now than</i>
<i> Sawchuk was when he joined us.</i>

1:01:55.879 --> 1:01:58.346
- Boston's not
so bad, Terry.

1:01:58.348 --> 1:02:01.316
Unless we get
those funny accents.

1:02:01.318 --> 1:02:03.368
You don't think
little Jerry and Jr.

1:02:03.369 --> 1:02:05.419
<i> are going to speak with</i>
<i> those accents do you? Bowston.</i>

1:02:05.422 --> 1:02:07.456
- I'm serious.

1:02:07.458 --> 1:02:09.908
I'm serious.

1:02:09.909 --> 1:02:12.359
Call the school and complain
if the kids talk like that.

1:02:13.931 --> 1:02:15.897
It's not right.

1:02:15.899 --> 1:02:18.166
You were all so
close in Detroit and

1:02:18.168 --> 1:02:19.868
then to hear about
it from your parents--

1:02:22.106 --> 1:02:23.722
Fantastic.

1:02:23.723 --> 1:02:25.339
Clean that up before
your kid crawls in it.

1:02:25.342 --> 1:02:27.008
- He doesn't even
know how to crawl.

1:02:27.010 --> 1:02:28.043
- Jack's not your family.

1:02:28.045 --> 1:02:30.779
We're your family.
He used you.

1:02:30.781 --> 1:02:32.414
- He needed me.

1:02:32.415 --> 1:02:34.048
<i> - Jack is a guy who got</i>
<i> you to shatter your bones</i>

1:02:34.051 --> 1:02:35.918
<i> to line his pocket.</i>

1:02:35.919 --> 1:02:37.786
- You don't know what
you're talking about.

1:02:40.290 --> 1:02:42.324
- You didn't get paid
as much as Gordie.

1:02:42.326 --> 1:02:44.025
Colleen let that slip.

1:03:00.477 --> 1:03:03.245
- Old elbow's acting up again.

1:03:03.914 --> 1:03:07.149
My friend, Audrey,
she's a nurse,

1:03:07.151 --> 1:03:09.551
<i> she says when a</i>
<i> bone doesn't set right,</i>

1:03:09.553 --> 1:03:11.953
it'll hurt forever.

1:03:11.955 --> 1:03:13.822
- Well, can't blame
this one on Jack.

1:03:13.824 --> 1:03:16.024
It happened
when I was a kid.

1:03:16.026 --> 1:03:17.559
I never had it set.

1:03:17.561 --> 1:03:19.127
- You're parents didn't?

1:03:19.129 --> 1:03:21.263
- Uh, they didn't know.

1:03:22.366 --> 1:03:25.033
They didn't like weakness.
Especially in kids.

1:03:26.003 --> 1:03:28.837
What, your father'd whup you
if you broke your arm?

1:03:28.839 --> 1:03:30.305
- My mother was worse.

1:03:30.307 --> 1:03:32.974
- Well, I believe that.

1:03:32.976 --> 1:03:35.377
I'm going to put you down.

1:03:38.015 --> 1:03:39.981
- Hey, buddy.

1:03:42.019 --> 1:03:43.351
- He's sleepy.

1:03:57.568 --> 1:04:00.869
- I ever tell you
about Lady's puppies?

1:04:02.005 --> 1:04:04.539
When I tried to
bring 'em back to life?

1:04:04.541 --> 1:04:06.174
- Magic?

1:04:06.176 --> 1:04:08.343
- Woodstove.

1:04:08.345 --> 1:04:10.946
<i> Our dog had, um,</i>

1:04:10.948 --> 1:04:13.615
<i> her puppies</i>
<i> under the porch.</i>

1:04:14.418 --> 1:04:17.419
50 below winter.

1:04:17.421 --> 1:04:20.055
And she wanted in but

1:04:20.057 --> 1:04:21.923
fat chance of that
in the Sawchuk household,

1:04:21.925 --> 1:04:23.391
they barely let us in.

1:04:28.565 --> 1:04:31.566
I remember those puppies.

1:04:33.136 --> 1:04:36.104
<i> Raw little chicken things,</i>

1:04:38.008 --> 1:04:40.442
<i> frozen to</i> the--

1:04:40.444 --> 1:04:43.211
to the wood beam.

1:04:43.213 --> 1:04:46.281
I tried to-I tried to
not tear their little legs.

1:04:49.453 --> 1:04:53.221
Mom wouldn't have a three-legged
dog, not like you, Pat.

1:04:55.292 --> 1:04:58.460
I got taught a
lesson that day, boy.

1:05:01.565 --> 1:05:04.900
That dog just wandered
in circles for days.

1:05:04.902 --> 1:05:06.468
For days.

1:05:07.371 --> 1:05:09.371
You could--

1:05:09.373 --> 1:05:12.641
You could trace
its path in the snow

1:05:12.643 --> 1:05:14.342
in blood.

1:05:18.482 --> 1:05:22.284
I never saw grief in my
mother's eyes like I did--

1:05:22.286 --> 1:05:25.153
Like I did in that dog's.

1:05:28.525 --> 1:05:32.360
Not even when Mitch--

1:05:35.966 --> 1:05:38.033
Not even when Mitch, uh...

1:05:38.035 --> 1:05:40.268
- When Mitch died.

1:05:49.413 --> 1:05:53.415
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm gonna wake the baby.

1:05:53.417 --> 1:05:54.983
- He's used to your
temper tantrums,

1:05:54.985 --> 1:05:56.384
he'll sleep
right through.

1:05:56.386 --> 1:05:58.219
- My temper tantrums?
- I was just making light.

1:05:58.221 --> 1:05:59.621
- You're always
saying that to me.

1:05:59.623 --> 1:06:00.722
- I'm sorry, Terry.

1:06:00.724 --> 1:06:02.991
- Why would you
say that to me?

1:06:02.992 --> 1:06:05.259
Don't try and make me stay
when you know I gotta go

1:06:05.262 --> 1:06:06.728
'cause I'm going
to regret something

1:06:06.730 --> 1:06:08.096
if you try and
make me fucking stay!

1:06:08.098 --> 1:06:10.131
- Please don't go.

1:06:22.045 --> 1:06:24.596
- Another one.

1:06:24.597 --> 1:06:27.148
- I wonder if you haven't
had enough there, sir?

1:06:28.285 --> 1:06:31.720
Why, Davy, this
is Mr. Terry Sawchuk,

1:06:31.722 --> 1:06:34.456
Boston's very famous goalie.

1:06:34.458 --> 1:06:36.758
What if downing a bottle
the night before a game

1:06:36.760 --> 1:06:38.660
is what makes him so good.

1:06:38.662 --> 1:06:40.562
Hm?

1:06:40.564 --> 1:06:43.298
Maybe bourbon is
his little secret.

1:06:43.300 --> 1:06:45.100
- Now I have to kill you.

1:06:45.102 --> 1:06:47.769
- That's a great pick-up line.

1:06:47.771 --> 1:06:51.172
Don't worry,
I'll get him home.

1:06:56.480 --> 1:06:58.113
And that one?

1:07:01.351 --> 1:07:02.717
- Henri Richard.

1:07:06.390 --> 1:07:08.757
And that one?

1:07:08.759 --> 1:07:10.692
- Nesterenko.

1:07:10.694 --> 1:07:13.595
<i> Game four of</i>
<i> the '52 series.</i>

1:07:13.597 --> 1:07:15.663
<i> - How about the bruises?</i>

1:07:16.800 --> 1:07:19.334
- Practice.

1:07:20.704 --> 1:07:23.204
<i> - And the shiner?</i>

1:07:24.241 --> 1:07:26.241
- Practice.

1:07:26.243 --> 1:07:28.209
- You okay?

1:07:28.211 --> 1:07:30.178
- Yeah.

1:07:37.721 --> 1:07:39.421
I, uh...

1:07:42.526 --> 1:07:44.526
- Oh.

1:07:46.496 --> 1:07:48.630
- I'll see ya'.
- Yeah.

1:07:49.399 --> 1:07:51.166
Look for me
on the ice, sweetheart!

1:07:51.168 --> 1:07:53.568
I'll be the one
wearing number 25.

1:07:56.106 --> 1:07:57.605
<i>- Fucker.</i>
<i>- You're out, Cal!</i>

1:07:57.607 --> 1:07:58.773
- Fuck you.
Who says I'm out?

1:07:58.775 --> 1:08:00.542
- It's "don't touch
the floor", man!

1:08:00.544 --> 1:08:02.710
The rules<i> are in the title.</i>

1:08:04.114 --> 1:08:05.647
- He's still got it.

1:08:05.649 --> 1:08:07.549
Richard! Richard!

1:08:07.551 --> 1:08:11.086
<i> - You dropped him, Ross!</i>
That's a fucking disgrace.

1:08:11.088 --> 1:08:12.554
<i> Do you like my belt?</i>

1:08:12.556 --> 1:08:14.656
- Oh, Jesus.
Get that away from me!

1:08:14.658 --> 1:08:16.424
Hey! Gardner! Gardner!

1:08:16.426 --> 1:08:17.425
Do you like my-- Ow!!

1:08:21.731 --> 1:08:24.833
- Willie, I just need
my hair, man.<i> Aw, fuck!</i>

1:08:24.835 --> 1:08:27.168
- End of the fucking world.

1:08:27.170 --> 1:08:28.820
<i> In hockey news,</i>

1:08:28.821 --> 1:08:30.471
<i> Terry Sawchuk takes on</i>
<i> his old team tonight</i>

1:08:30.474 --> 1:08:32.273
<i> as Boston heads to Detroit.</i>

1:09:06.776 --> 1:09:10.145
<i>Sawchuk! Sawchuk!</i>
<i> Sawchuk! Sawchuk!</i>

1:09:20.724 --> 1:09:22.490
- There he is.

1:09:22.492 --> 1:09:25.360
Hey, there.
Come have a seat, son.

1:09:26.696 --> 1:09:28.596
- I, um...

1:09:28.598 --> 1:09:30.431
That's for the shoes.

1:09:30.433 --> 1:09:32.233
- What?

1:09:32.235 --> 1:09:35.236
- I never paid you back.
I don't like owing people.

1:09:40.677 --> 1:09:43.178
- Come on, now.
Sit down, please.

1:09:45.649 --> 1:09:47.415
- Oh, uh...

1:09:49.686 --> 1:09:52.187
- Okay, I traded you.

1:09:52.689 --> 1:09:55.323
It's a team, not a family.

1:09:55.825 --> 1:09:59.227
- I never thought
it was a family.

1:10:01.731 --> 1:10:04.532
- You weren't the only one
worried about his job.

1:10:04.534 --> 1:10:07.835
It's a shit part
of mine too, you know.

1:10:07.837 --> 1:10:10.338
If I were a cattle farmer,

1:10:10.340 --> 1:10:13.942
feeding and looking
after calves and cows every day

1:10:13.944 --> 1:10:16.945
and one of them
stands out, a great one,

